BUG REPORT
  file: greet.go
  line: 10
  lens: nil-safety/error-handling
  severity: high
  title: Nil pointer dereference on cfg parameter
  description: Greeting dereferences cfg (cfg.Name) without checking for nil. Any caller passing a nil *Config will trigger a runtime panic with a nil pointer dereference. The function is exported (capital G) so it is part of the public API and nil is a trivially reachable argument.
  reporter's evidence: func Greeting(cfg *Config) string {
    return "hello " + cfg.Name
} (greet.go:9-10) — cfg has type *Config, no nil guard before the field access on line 10; nil is a valid value for a *Config argument to an exported function.


